summary:
I am a mathematician/software developer currently working as a Senior AI Engineer at Capgemini.

I have a double Bachelor's degree in Mathematics and Physics. In addition, I completed the master's programme Mathematics, Statistics and Big Data, with the judicium Cum Laude and my master's thesis was graded with a 9. During my master's degree my focus was mainly on machine learning and data analysis and automation.

I have a lot of experience in programming. I am fluent in Flutter (mobile app development) as well as R (statistical programming). Moreover, I have worked with many other widely-used languages, toolkits and databases (Vue, Python, C, C#, Java, Firebase, SQL, Unity). I have worked in several projects with cloud computing, specifically Azure.

After many software projects, I co-founded Delooye. At Delooye we build custom software for small and medium businesses. Delooye was founded not too long ago, but has already successfully completed a few big projects. Within the company I am mainly responsible for frontend development, mathematical modeling and analysis, and customer relations.

See my github page (https://github.com/jorispdejong) for some projects in R. Other types of projects are not shown, because they are private or in collaboration with others, but I am happy to share them on request.
